SIMPLE: excellently
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Excellently
<hw>Ex"cel*lent*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In an
excellent manner; well in a high degree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a high or superior degree; -- in this literal
use, not implying worthiness.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When the whole heart is <qex>excellently</qex> sorry.</q>
<rj><qau>J. Fletcher.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excelsior</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
